text: Saiful Muluk National Park () is located in the Kaghan Valley in Mansehra District of Khyber-Pakhtunkhwa, in northern Pakistan. The park was created in 2003. Some of the park's fauna includes the snow leopard, asiatic black bear, marmot, weasel, eurasian lynx, indian leopard, Himalayan snowcock, and the snow partridge. Lulusar-Dudipatsar National Park is close to Saiful Muluk National Park. == Related pages == * Mansehra District Category:National parks in Pakistan Category:Mansehra District
